properties.headline: Flood Watch issued February 5 at 4:16AM EST until February 6 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Jackson KY
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Jackson has expanded the

* Flood Watch to include portions of east central Kentucky,
northeast Kentucky, and southeast Kentucky, including the
following counties, in east central Kentucky, Estill. In
northeast Kentucky, Johnson and Martin. In southeast Kentucky,
Breathitt, Floyd, Knott, Lee, Magoffin, Pike, and Wolfe.

* The Flood Watch is in effect from this evening through Thursday
morning.

* Another round of widespread heavier rainfall will be possible
this evening and tonight, continuing into Thursday, as a storm
system approaches eastern Kentucky. This additional heavy
rainfall, on top of saturated soils, will likely lead to at
least isolated flooding.

* Minor flooding of low lying areas, as well as rivers, creeks,
and streams will be possible.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Watch means there is a potential for flooding based on
current forecasts.

You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible
Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be
prepared to take action should flooding develop.

NWSheadline: FLOOD WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING
